{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"S4 SWEEP HIT-LIST (repo-wide, excl .git/.venv/.tickets-tracker/node_modules; patterns: pull request, gh pr, open a PR, merge the PR, PR merge, single change, one change at a time, refs/for/main). RESULT: sweep is CLEAN — zero unjustified hits. The feature-branch flow is an ADDITION, not a correction; every refs/for/main is a correct single-change instruction.\n\nFIX (1 genuine staleness, outside S4's enumerated file list — will fix here or via follow-up): infra/runbooks/github-mirror-lock.md:234-236 embeds an OLD single-vote gate spec ('label:LLM-Review=MAX AND -has:unresolved') predating the two-vote gate — update to two-vote wording.\nBORDERLINE (optional): CLAUDE.md:31 'open a PR' generic start-work phrasing in a Gerrit-only repo (low priority).\n\nJUSTIFIED (correct as-is, no change): CLAUDE.md:424/444/460 (mirror ruleset / deliberate counter-example / correct single-change push); CONTRIBUTING.md:14/88-92/140/158/179 (single-change loop + mirror lock); README.md:248; docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md:27/490-492/522 (mirror-lock mechanics + topology); infra/runbooks/github-mirror-lock.md:11-13/97-98/200/233 (lock verification steps); two-vote-gate-rollback.md:116; reviewbot-e2e.sh:301 + apply-mirror-lock.sh:12-14 (mirror-lock comments); docs/adr/0004:26 + several tests/* (substring false positives).\n\nVERIFY (§5 AC): README.md, docs/local-dev-env.md, docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md all confirmed CURRENT for the two-vote + feature-branch world (gerrit-aws-setup §6/§6a already documents the feature-branch flow + ADR 0025; its cross-ref to review-bot-ops 'signals to watch' resolves once the review-bot-ops merge-change section lands). Zero unjustified hits remain."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783110519251009001,"uuid":"6b37eff1-ade0-40f6-bac5-f385037f62c2"}